# Security

## Secrets & Environment Variables
- NEVER hardcode API keys, tokens, passwords, or endpoints in source code
- Use `import.meta.env.VITE_*` for all client-side config (strings, endpoints)
- All secrets live in `.env.local` (gitignored) or GitHub Actions Secrets
- Never commit `.env.local`, `.env.*.local`, or any file containing real credentials
- Always guard env vars: `if (!ENDPOINT) { setError('Not configured'); return }`

## Input & Output
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` — all content goes through React's JSX escaping
- Sanitize nothing that comes out of our own translation files (trusted static data)
- Validate user input at the boundary only (form submission), not deeper in the stack
- Form data is sent via `fetch` to Formspree; Formspree handles server-side validation

## External Links
- Every `target="_blank"` link must have `rel="noopener noreferrer"` — already enforced in the codebase
- External image sources used in canvas require `crossOrigin="anonymous"` (already in Works.tsx)

## Dependencies
- Run `npm audit` before merging any PR that changes `package.json`
- Never install a package from an unknown publisher or with < 10k weekly downloads
- Prefer the approved stack (see packages.mdc) over adding new dependencies

## Git hygiene
- `dist/`, `node_modules/`, `.env.local` are in `.gitignore` — never force-add them
- Never push API keys, tokens, or credentials to any branch, including feature branches
- If a secret is accidentally committed: rotate the secret immediately, then clean git history
